How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Great t-shirts, Not so great packaging design.
We buy Hanes for the convenience and consistent quality. These t-shirts are great as are other Hanes products. To Hanes the company, I will echo the same sentiment others are not appreciating; this "Feel the Softness" open hole on the front of the pack is simply unnecessary and unsanitary with dirt and debrit that makes it's way inside. We wash them prior to wearing, but @Hanes if they see this, please consider basic fully enclosed packaging without this hole! We work hard for the big and little things we purchase in life. Other than that, zero complaints, awesome t-shirts. Thanks

kristin
5.0 out of 5 stars Great Basic T-shirts
Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2024
Size: X-LargeColor: Black/Grey/Blue Assorted - 6 PackNumber of Items: 6Verified Purchase
These make excellent basic t-shirts to have on hand. 6 pack was $11.50. At under $2 a shirt, it's a great deal for a name brand.
The colors were the ones men wear alot of: Grey, navy, black.
These can be undershirts or worn as a t-shirt. They are good quality material. Not too thin or see thru.
I purchased a pack of Large & a pack of X-large. Noticeable size difference when held side by side. Fit is true to size, running on the side of a the looser fit.
I always soak dark cottons in white vinegar prior to washing the first time, to prevent fading & bleeding. These haven't faded after washing. Not sure if it's because of the vinegar soak or the fabric quality. But I've had no issue with fading.
The fabric is cotton. Softens after the first wash.
My son's usually wear these until I have to turn them into cleaning rags, so I know from previous experience that they hold up & last for several years.
Great purchase....especially on sale!

Shay
4.0 out of 5 stars Okay undershirts for the price.
Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2024
Size: LargeColor: White - 3 PackNumber of Items: 3Verified Purchase
I recently purchased a 3-pack of white shirts, and overall, they serve their purpose well as undershirts.

Firstly, let's talk about the material. The shirts are made of a thin fabric, which makes them ideal for layering underneath other clothing. They are lightweight and breathable, which is perfect for wearing under dress shirts or sweaters without adding bulk.

In terms of sizing, I found that they look a bit big when you first take them out of the packaging. However, once worn, they fit pretty close to the expected size. They provide a comfortable fit without being overly tight or restrictive.

The quality of the shirts is decent for the price. While they may not be the most durable shirts for everyday wear on their own, they hold up well as undershirts. The stitching seems sturdy, and after a few washes, they have maintained their shape and color.

One thing to note is that because they are white shirts, they may require more frequent washing to keep them looking crisp and clean.

Overall, if you're looking for affordable, basic white shirts primarily for layering purposes, this 3-pack is a good option. They are comfortable, fit well once worn, and serve their intended function as undershirts effectively. I would recommend them for anyone needing reliable undershirts without breaking the bank.

Adam
5.0 out of 5 stars Hanes Vs. Fruit of the Loom Undershirts
Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2024
Size: XX-LargeColor: White - 3 PackNumber of Items: 3Verified Purchase
This review is for those of you trying to decide between the Hanes vs. Fruit of the Loom undershirts.
Overall, I have to go with Hanes because the neck hole feels more appropriate. Fruit of the Loom is just too large. At the end of the day, the hole will stretch out and show chest hair popping up in the front, and back hair from the back.
If the goal is to wear an undershirt for work with a business casual dress shirt (top button open / no tie) I don't want my chest cleavage showing; otherwise I'd get a V-neck.

The Hanes shirt is thinner and cooler. BUT, it's also a bit more rough / scratchy. Not in a bad way, but Fruit of the Loom feels super soft in comparison.

I'll also mention that after one wear I started noticing threads coming out of the arm seams on the Hanes, whereas Fruit of the Loom have gone through multiple washes and are still as durable as the day I got them. The Hanes haven't fallen apart by any means, but it's something to point out.

Both a 2X Hanes and 2XL Fruit of the Loom seem to be the same length. I have a big gut, so I was worried not having the "[L]ong" affix for a size option for Hanes meant they would be too short and hard to tuck into my pants, but they tuck great even after washing.

Both are great options tbh. In summary -
Hanes for:
- Smaller neck
- Cooler / lighter fit
Fruit of the Loom for:
- Softer / warmer fit
- More durability
